    m_VerticalOverflow: 1
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "The Evaluator supports operations: +, -, *, /.\nUnary minus is also supported,
    but a negative number must be surrounded by brackets. (Inspired by the MS Windows
    calculator).\nIf an unbalanced (odd) number of brackets is used, an error text
    will be displayed below.\nYou can use \".\" and \",\" as decimal separators.\nYou
    can use \\ as a division sign - it is auto-replaced. (Yes, it's not entirely
    correct, but usually guys don't know the difference).\nIt does not attempt to
    divide by zero - it throws an error.\nTheoretically, special characters, like
    \\n, can be thrown into the string and break everything. For this reason, I abandoned
    the idea of using a compiler\\expression tree. \n\nAt the beginning of the ExpressionEvaluator
    script, there is a list of materials used.\nThe assignment states: Unity GUI.
    In versions 2017+, it cannot be used even as a joke; for example, my graphics
    card \"blacks out\".\nTherefore, I used UI. If needed, I will redo it. "
