    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "The Evaluator supports operations: +, -, *, /.\r\nUnary minus is also
    supported, but a negative number must be surrounded by brackets. (Inspired by
    the MS Windows calculator).\r\nIf an unbalanced (odd) number of brackets is used,
    an error text will be displayed below.\r\nYou can use \".\" and \",\" as decimal
    separators.\r\nYou can use \\ as a division sign - it is auto-replaced. (Yes,
    it's not entirely correct, but usually guys don't know the difference).\r\nIt
    does not attempt to divide by zero - it throws an error.\r\nTheoretically, special
    characters, like \\n, can be thrown into the string and break everything. For
    this reason, I abandoned the idea of using a compiler\\expression tree. \r\n\r\nAt
    the beginning of the ExpressionEvaluator script, there is a list of materials
    used.\r\nThe assignment states: Unity GUI. In versions 2017+, it cannot be used
    even as a joke; for example, my graphics card \"blacks out\".\r\nTherefore, I
    used UI. If needed, I will redo it. "
